Gunmen have kidnapped one Dr. Wisdom Iboyitete, the resident doctor of the Central Hospital, Ojobo in Burutu Local Government Area of Delta State. The incident happened on Sunday night, causing tension in the coastal community, it was gathered. A source said the doctor had received an emergency call from the hospital and was rushing to attend to the case when he was whisked away through the creeks by the hoodlums. Commissioner of Police Hafiz Inuwa confirmed the incident, adding that the kidnappers had pretended to be patients who needed the services of the doctor. “Yes. The people posed as patients, so the doctor was to treat them. They kidnapped him and took him inside the water. Maybe they came with a boat. But we have mobilised policemen to that place to see what they can do,” he said. In Niger State, three suspected kidnappers of seven persons including five female students of Tular Academy in Mariga council of the state have been arrested. On March 3, bandits abducted five schoolgirls, their teacher and a security man at Tular Academy, a private secondary boarding school. The Nation learnt that the kidnapped victims were released by their kidnappers after N2.3 million ransom was paid. Police spokesman Abiodun Wasiu confirmed the arrests, adding that the suspects had shared the ransom cash before their arrest. He said that efforts were on to arrest other members of the syndicate.